{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ῥῆσις</b>, εως, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> ιος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD(?): Arcadius Grammaticus \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>] <b>ϝρῆσις</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(“IG” 5(2).343.19, Orchom., 4th c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], ἡ, (ἐρῶ) <b>saying, speech</b>, μύθων καὶ ῥήσιος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.291; ῥ. ἀγγελῶν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 1.59 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; καταπλέξαι τὴν ῥῆσιν end one's <b>speech</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.83; ῥ. βραχεῖα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 64; ξυνεχής 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.85; μακρὰν ῥ. οὐ στέργει πόλις 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 273; εἰπεῖν ῥ. οὐ θρῆνον θέλω [prev. author] “Ag.” 1322; ῥ. λέγειν ἀμφί τινος [prev. author] “Supp.” 615, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 142.20; περὶ σμικροῦ πράγματος ῥ. παμμήκεις ποιεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 268c; μακρὰν ῥ. ἀποτείνειν [prev. author] “R.” 605d, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Prom.” 6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ ἀπὸ Σκυθῶν ῥ. the Scythian <b>answer</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.127 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (a phrase that became proverbial,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Prov.” 1.62; probably interpolated in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>resolution, declaration</b>, Λακεδαιμονίων ῥ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.152, compare 5th c.BC: Crates Comicus 56, “IG” [prev. cited] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>speaking</b>, opposed to reading (ἀνάγνωσις), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Isocrate” 2 (Wolf, for χρήσεως). \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>tale, legend</b>, ἀνθρώπων παλαιαὶ ῥ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 7.55. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>expression</b> or <b>passage</b> in an author, especially <b>speech in a play</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1371, “V.” 580, “Ra.” 151, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Ἐπιτρέποντες” 585: _plural_ in 4th c.BC: Ephippus Comicus 16.3, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.267; ῥ. τινὲς τῶν Ἀριστοφανείων 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.712d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially of the dramatic parts of epic poetry, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9th c.AD: Photius Legal icographus, etc. \">Refs 9th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>manner of speaking, style</b>, ἡ κατὰ πεζὸν ῥ. <b>prose</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Longinus Rhetor “Prolegomena ad Hephaestionis Euchiridion” 1.3. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9022","accentedUnicode":"ῥῆσις","shortDef":"a saying","mediumDef":"a saying","stepGloss":"a saying","stepTransliteration":"rēsis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}